ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a great introduction to the work being done across the university in European Studies. IT's a good class to take if you want that kind of quick and comprehensive introduction.

I believe that this course gives a great overview of the various aspects to European and Russian Studies. I liked this course because it exposed me to professors and topics that I would otherwise not have had the opportunity to encounter.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It gave me a broader appreciation for what I could research for the thesis next year.
This course did not contribute to my research, but I believe it was a valuable course to take, as it broadened my perspective of the European and Russian Studies discipline.
